#: ../../source/Stability.rst:2
msgid "Stability policy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Stability.rst:4
msgid ""
"PREP-SHOT's stability surface evolves across major versions. Each major "
"version makes a different promise about what is allowed to break."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Stability.rst:8
msgid "v1.x -- research / evolving (current)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Stability.rst:10
msgid ""
"Use v1.x for active research; pin to a specific tag (e.g. ``v1.1.0``) for"
" any reproducible study."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Stability.rst:13
msgid ""
"The Python entry point ``prepshot.create_model(params)`` is **stable**; "
"arguments and return type will not change in v1.x."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Stability.rst:15
msgid ""
"The ``params.json`` input schema is **evolving** and tracked by "
"``_schema_version`` (currently ``1``). Breaking changes can land on minor"
" version bumps within v1.x. See the Changelog page for each bump."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Stability.rst:18
msgid ""
"The ``prepshot/_model/`` sub-package internals (constraint classes, rule "
"methods) are **internal**; they may change without notice."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Stability.rst:22
msgid "v2.0 -- stable (planned)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Stability.rst:24
msgid "When the input schema and Python API both feel right:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Stability.rst:26
msgid "Both surfaces will be promised stable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Stability.rst:27
msgid "Breaking changes will require a major version bump."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Stability.rst:28
msgid ""
"A migration registry (``prepshot/migrations/``) will be in place so that "
"future schema bumps come with automated migrations."
msgstr ""

